         <abstract>
            <p>One of the occupational hazards of portfolio management is that even the best portfolio manager can occasionally go wrong on any given security. Yet despite--or possibly because of--his fallibility, it is a rare portfolio manager that keeps score on himself. The author presents a questionnaire with which, by answering all questions candidly, the portfolio manager can rate his own performance.</p>
